==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dead-stroke
<hw>Dead"-stroke`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Mech.)</fld>
<def>Making a stroke without recoil; deadbeat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Dead-stroke hammer</b></col> <fld>(Mach.)</fld>, <cd>a
power hammer having a spring interposed between the driving mechanism
and the hammer head, or helve, to lessen the recoil of the hammer and
reduce the shock upon the mechanism.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deadwood</ent>⟦br⟧
